<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDEFFB33FAFFE80FC15FE06" blockId="1.[174,1232,341,560]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
F e m a l e. Body length 
<quantity id="4C8B9B66FFDEFFB33EA0FE80FDAAFEA6" box="[492,633,341,368]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="2.1">2.1–2.4 mm</quantity>
, 
<typeStatus id="54C88821FFDEFFB33DC8FE80FD38FEA6" box="[644,747,341,368]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity id="4C8B9B66FFDEFFB33DBDFE80FC9EFEA6" box="[753,845,341,368]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
. Head, mesosoma and metasoma black, antennae, including scape and flagellum black, coxae black, hind and mid femur and tibia black, fore femur black, but fore tibia some dark yellow at the apex, tarsi of all legs brownish-yellow; tip of ovipositor black; veins of fore wings yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDEFFB03FAFFE00FCBCFE5C" blockId="1.[174,1232,341,560]" lastBlockId="2.[166,1225,175,810]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="109" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Head (dorsally) wider than its length (ratio 1.90: 1); wider than pronotum; temple in dorsal view shorter than length of eye (1: 1.41). Head (in frontal view) broader than high (ratio 1.48: 1); malar space some shorter than height of eye (1: 1.15). External margin of clypeus straight, eyes bare; face and vertex with fine reticulation, lower face with short white sparse pubescence. Antennae inserted lower than middle part of face; scape not reaching the mid ocellus, short and stout; pedicel much shorter than 1st funicular segment; annellus very short; 1st funicular segment long, much longer than following funicular segments, almost 2.0 times longer than 2nd segment (18: 10); 2nd flagellar segment transverse; 3nd–5th almost quadrate; club long and stout, 3-segmented, wider than previous flagellar segments; flagellum with very short, pale, sparse pubescence.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF0C660BFFDEFFB33FE3F920FDA1F897" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404259" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6404259" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404259/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" startId="1.[175,208,1781,1803]" targetBox="[248,1163,624,1744]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDEFFB33FE3F920FDA1F897" blockId="1.[174,1233,1781,1857]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">
Fig. 1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D00FFDEFFB33FA1F920FD88F8DD" authority="Zerova et Ayad Al-Sendi" authorityName="Zerova et Ayad Al-Sendi" authorityYear="2019" box="[237,603,1781,1803]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Systole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irana" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDEFFB33FA1F920FEB4F8DD" box="[237,359,1781,1803]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Systole irana</emphasis>
Zerova et Ayad Al-Sendi
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23457EAFFDEFFB33D28F920FD4BF8DD" box="[612,664,1781,1803]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDEFFB33DEBF920FD19F8DD" box="[679,714,1781,1803]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">1–4</emphasis>
— female, holotype; 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDEFFB33CD9F920FC73F8DD" box="[917,928,1781,1803]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">1</emphasis>
— adult, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDEFFB33B39F920FB53F8DD" box="[1141,1152,1781,1803]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">2</emphasis>
— head and thorax dorsally; 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDEFFB33E34F8C5FE50F8F0" box="[376,387,1808,1830]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">3</emphasis>
— antenna; 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDEFFB33D4EF8C5FDDEF8F0" box="[514,525,1808,1830]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">4</emphasis>
— fore wing venation; 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDEFFB33DBAF8C5FCD2F8F0" box="[758,769,1808,1830]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">5</emphasis>
—head, frontal view; 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D00FFDEFFB33C96F8C5FF21F897" authority="Zerova et Fursov" authorityName="Zerova et Fursov" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Systole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dzintari" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDEFFB33C96F8C5FBBEF8F0" box="[986,1133,1808,1830]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">Systole dzintari</emphasis>
Zerova et Fursov
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23457EAFFDEFFB33FB7F8FEFEFCF897" box="[251,303,1835,1857]" pageId="1" pageNumber="108" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype: 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDEFFB33ED5F8FEFE77F897" box="[409,420,1835,1857]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="108">6</emphasis>
—head, frontal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDDFFB03F97FE5AFB79FDFC" blockId="2.[166,1225,175,810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Mesosoma slightly bulging (in lateral view); pronotal collar transverse, very short, ratio of width to length 4: 1, twice shorter than mesoscutum; scutellum as long as mesoscutum; mesosoma dorsally finely reticulated. Propodeum steeped, without median furrow with irregular wrinkles. Legs rather stout, coxae elongate, hind coxa finely reticulate. Disc of forewing with very sparse and hardly visible pilosity. Ratio of marginal, postmarginal and radial veins: 1: 1.09: 1.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDDFFB03F97FDFAFB74FD5C" blockId="2.[166,1225,175,810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Metasoma with very short annellus; abdomen (in lateral view) longer than mesosoma (ratio 1.59: 1); apex of abdomen upturned. 4th abdominal segment the longest; surface of tergites almost bare, only with some short bristles on 4th–6th segments and epipygium.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDDFFB03F97FD5AFE7CFD7C" blockId="2.[166,1225,175,810]" box="[219,431,655,682]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">M a l e not known.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDDFFB03F97FD7AFC62FCFF" blockId="2.[166,1225,175,810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">
D i a g n o s i s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D00FFDDFFB03E3AFD7AFDBFFD1F" authority="Zerova &amp; Al-Sendi &amp; Fursov &amp; Adeli-Manesh &amp; Sadeghi &amp; Pirouzi, 2019" authorityName="Zerova &amp; Al-Sendi &amp; Fursov &amp; Adeli-Manesh &amp; Sadeghi &amp; Pirouzi" authorityYear="2019" box="[374,620,687,714]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Systole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irana" status="sp.n." subGenus="Systole">
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDDFFB03E3AFD7AFE17FD1F" box="[374,452,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Systole</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDDFFB03E9EFD7AFDF3FD1F" box="[466,544,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Systole</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDDFFB03D61FD65FDBFFD1F" box="[557,620,688,713]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">irana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23457EAFFDDFFB03D23FD7AFD7AFD1C" box="[623,681,687,714]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D00FFDDFFB03C7EFD65FBCBFD1C" authority="Zerova" authorityName="Zerova" authorityYear="1972" box="[818,1048,687,714]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Systole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prangicola">
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDDFFB03C7EFD65FC10FD1F" box="[818,963,687,714]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">S.prangicola</emphasis>
Zerova
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D00FFDDFFB03B07FD65FF28FD3C" authority="Zerova" authorityName="Zerova" authorityYear="1970" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Systole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDDFFB03B07FD65FB1AFD1F" box="[1099,1225,687,714]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">S. elongata</emphasis>
Zerova
</taxonomicName>
, which also have a long 1st funicular segment in female. 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D00FFDDFFB03CD1FD1AFBE1FD3F" authority="Zerova &amp; Al-Sendi &amp; Fursov &amp; Adeli-Manesh &amp; Sadeghi &amp; Pirouzi, 2019" authorityName="Zerova &amp; Al-Sendi &amp; Fursov &amp; Adeli-Manesh &amp; Sadeghi &amp; Pirouzi" authorityYear="2019" box="[925,1074,719,745]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Systole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irana" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDDFFB03CD1FD1AFBE1FD3F" box="[925,1074,719,745]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Systole irana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23457EAFFDDFFB03B75FD1AFBA4FD3C" box="[1081,1143,719,746]" pageId="2" pageNumber="109" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from them by the distinctive upturned apex of abdomen in female. Specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F3647613FFDDFFB03BDBFD3AFB1AFCDC" box="[1175,1225,751,778]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="109">Iran</collectingCountry>
