</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDCFFB13FAFFB63FC8FFA87" blockId="3.[174,1232,1206,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
Diagnosis. New species is close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D00FFDCFFB13DDEFB62FC16FB07" authority="Zerova et Gam" authorityName="Zerova et Gam" box="[658,965,1206,1233]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Systole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDCFFB13DDEFB62FCD9FB06" box="[658,778,1207,1233]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">S. minima</emphasis>
Zerova et Ģam
</taxonomicName>
, which also has yellow antennae, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D00FFDCFFB13E11FB02FE09FB26" authority="Zerova &amp; Al-Sendi &amp; Fursov &amp; Adeli-Manesh &amp; Sadeghi &amp; Pirouzi, 2019" authorityName="Zerova &amp; Al-Sendi &amp; Fursov &amp; Adeli-Manesh &amp; Sadeghi &amp; Pirouzi" authorityYear="2019" box="[349,474,1238,1265]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Systole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dzintari" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDCFFB13E11FB02FE09FB26" box="[349,474,1238,1265]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">S. dzintari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23457EAFFDCFFB13EA9FB03FDF4FB27" box="[485,551,1238,1265]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from this species by the structure of antenna in female, which does not have the short 3rd segment; by shorter abdomen which is much shorter than mesosoma, but the abdomen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D00FFDCFFB13D85FAC2FC91FAE6" box="[713,834,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Systole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDCFFB13D85FAC2FC91FAE6" box="[713,834,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">S. minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as long as mesosoma. Specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F3647613FFDCFFB13FA3FAE3FEF2FA87" box="[239,289,1334,1361]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Iran</collectingCountry>
were compared with 
<typeStatus id="54C88821FFDCFFB13D52FAE3FD83FA87" box="[542,592,1334,1361]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C734D00FFDCFFB13D92FAE2FC86FA86" box="[734,853,1335,1361]" class="Insecta" family="Eurytomidae" genus="Systole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis id="B907EA91FFDCFFB13D92FAE2FC86FA86" box="[734,853,1335,1361]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">S. minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC3683FFDCFFB13FAFFA83FD84FA47" blockId="3.[174,1232,1206,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">E t h y m o l o g y. The species has light-yellow, amber-like antennae. Name “dzintari” means “amber” in Latvian language.</paragraph>
